      <div class="shell">
        <div class="section-head">
          <span class="tag">Engines</span>
          <h2>The part most apps never build.</h2>
          <p>
            CMS is strong because the logic underneath it is strong. These engines give the app
            its edge and make the promise believable.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="grid">
          <article class="card">
            <h3>Macrocycle Engine</h3>
            <p>
              CMS calculates how far out a competition is, then assembles the training flow from there.
              Hypertrophy, strength, peak, and taper blocks are not hand-waved. <span class="accent">They are built from time-to-meet.</span>
