            Bench Specialization, Jacked and Strong, and SBD are already built in. Your program will adapt as you train.
          </p>
          <div class="hero-actions">
            <a class="btn btn-primary" href="https://app.cmstrength.fit">Open The App</a>
            <a class="btn btn-secondary" href="#programs">View Programs</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="faq">
      <div class="shell">
        <div class="section-head">
          <span class="tag">FAQ</span>
          <h2>Questions lifters are going to ask.</h2>
        </div>

        <div class="grid">
          <article class="card">
            <h3>Is CMS only for one kind of lifter?</h3>
            <p>
              No. CMS supports three clear lanes right now: Bench Specialization, Jacked and Strong, and full SBD.
              That gives lifters a reason to join whether they care most about bench, size plus strength, or meet prep.
            </p>
          </article>
          <article class="card">
            <h3>What makes the programming different?</h3>
            <p>
              The engines. CMS uses competition-date macrocycle logic, readiness-based load adjustments, and lift-specific
              joint penalties to shape training instead of leaving everything static.
            </p>
          </article>
          <article class="card">
            <h3>Does the app actually adapt?</h3>
            <p>
              Yes. Feedback from check-ins changes assigned training loads, and the system already includes logic for
              block progression and weak-point-aware exercise alternatives.
            </p>
          </article>
          <article class="card">
            <h3>Can I track progress over time?</h3>
            <p>
              Yes. The analytics page shows e1RM trends for every lift, block-by-block progression, and a full training history.
              You can see exactly how you're moving week to week.
            </p>
          </article>
          <article class="card">
            <h3>Is there a free trial?</h3>
            <p>
              CMS is free to use while in Beta. Create an account, pick a program, and start training. No cards required, no paywall.
              We encourage feedback through our suggestions card.
            </p>
          </article>
          <article class="card">
            <h3>How do weak points work?</h3>
            <p>
              Tell the app where you're weak (lockout, mid-range, off-chest, or none), and it swaps exercises intelligently.
              Lockout weak? Smart lifters address weakness.
            </p>
